  "title": "Apple Q2 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-07-31T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q2",
  "location": "Cupertino, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.apple.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "tim-cook",
      "speaker_name": "Tim Cook",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "We are thrilled with our Q2 results. Services revenue set another all-time record at $27.8 billion, up 14%. The App Store saw its highest-ever developer earnings in a second quarter. We are announcing that Apple Vision Pro Gen 2 will ship in Q4 2025, with a new form factor that is 40% lighter and priced at $2,499 — meaningfully more accessible. Mac revenue grew 8% on the strength of the M4 Pro lineup. We expect Services to cross $110 billion in annual revenue this calendar year."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "kevan-parekh",
      "speaker_name": "Kevan Parekh",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total revenue was $89.2 billion, up 4% year-over-year. Gross margin was 47.4%. We returned $26.5 billion to shareholders. For Q3 2025, we expect revenue of $87–90 billion and a gross margin in the range of 47–48%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Ben Reitzes at Melius Research."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-ben-reitzes",
      "speaker_name": "Ben Reitzes",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Tim, Vision Pro Gen 2 at $2,499 is a bold pricing move. What gives you confidence that the addressable market expands meaningfully from the Gen 1 installed base?"
    }
  ],
